e (  Simon Zelotes ). ‘When Jesus beheld him, he said, Thou art Simon the son of Jona: thou shalt be called Cephas, which is by interpretation, A stone’ (John 1:42). According to Matthew 16:17–18, Christ says more explicitly, ‘Blessed art thou, Simon Bar-jona … thou art Peter, and upon this rock I will build my church’. The name has been in continuous use since the Middle Ages."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Pedro Paes de Ambia was born in 1154, in Leiria, Portugal as the son of Paio Ares de Ambiá. He had at least 1 daughter with María Fernandes de Gundiás."},"et":{"1154–":"1154–Surnud","1154–Male":"1154–Surnud","1553–Female":"1553–Surnud","1180–1235":"1180–1235","1130–Male":"1130–Surnud","1235":"1235","1553":"1553","1154":"1154","1130":"1130","1180":"1180","Leiria, Portugal":"Leiria, Portugal","Portugal":"Portugal"},"fi":{"1154–":"1154–Kuollut","1154–Male":"1154–Kuollut","1553–Female":"1553–Kuollut","1180–1235":"1180–1235","1130–Male":"1130–Kuollut","1235":"1235","1553":"1553","1154":"1154","1130":"1130","1180":"1180","Leiria, Portugal":"Leiria, Portugali","Portugal":"Portugali"},"fr":{"1154–":"1154–Décédé","1154–Male":"1154–Décédé","1553–Female":"1553–Décédée","1180–1235":"1180–1235","1130–Male":"1130–Décédé","1235":"1235","1553":"1553","1154":"1154","1130":"1130","1180":"1180","Leiria, Portugal":"Leiria, Portugal","Portugal":"Portugal","lifeSummary":"Pedro Paes de Ambia est né en 1154, à Leiria, Portugal, fils de Paio Ares de Ambiá. Il a eu au moins 1 fille avec María Fernandes de Gundiás."},"de":{"1154–":"1154–Verstorben","1154–Male":"1154–Verstorben","1553–Female":"1553–Verstorben","1180–1235":"1180–1235","1130–Male":"1130–Verstorben","1235":"1235","1553":"1553","1154":"1154","1130":"1130","1180":"1180","Leiria, Portugal":"Leiria, Portugal","Portugal":"Portugal","lifeSummary":"Pedro Paes de Ambia wurde 1154 in Leiria, Portugal, als Sohn von Paio Ares de Ambiá geboren. Er hatte mit María Fernandes de Gundiás mindestens 1 Tochter."},"ht":{"1154–":"1154–Desede","1154–Male":